{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place orange peel in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>4 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sugar and grind <nobr>30 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter, salt and egg then mix <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add flour and baking powder then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Wrap in cling film and place in fridge for 45 minutes.","Preheat oven to 180°C and line 2 baking trays with baking paper.","Cut dough in half, return half to fridge, then roll the other half on a floured work surface to approx. 3 mm thick.","Using a pastry wheel or a sharp knife, cut 25 squares (6 cm) and place on prepared baking trays.","Place ¾ tsp plum jam in the centre of squares of dough.","Cut each square from the 4 corners to the centre approximately 2 cm deep, so that 8 dough tips are created. Fold every second dough piece to the middle and squeeze slightly over the filling. Repeat with second half of the dough. Bake for 15 minutes (180°C).","Place Christmas wheels on a wire rack, leave to cool before serving or store in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["¼ orange, thin peelings of skin only","75 g sugar","120 g unsalted butter, cold, diced","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 medium egg","280 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","½ tsp baking powder","150 g plum jam"]}],"id":"r254888","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-HXJLlzucvYc\/XZWrR16ynkI\/AAAAAAAAfk8\/OrsrnlPlAxkkE5owgKJhKHTom6PxEFkjACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hfWrWbXDzl7i-EkF.png","title":"Plum Christmas Wheels","publishedAt":"2017-12-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"15 g","calories":"437 kJ \/ 104 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, baking trays, baking paper, rolling pin, pastry wheel or cutter, wire rack, airtight container, refrigerator, oven","basicInfo":["medium","45m","2h","25 pieces"]}